# E2E test env (loaded by `vite ... --mode test`). Committed on purpose: these
# are stub, non-secret values. The Supabase network layer is fully intercepted
# by the Playwright suite (e2e/support/mockDb.ts), so the URL never needs to be
# reachable. The host's first label ("stub") determines the supabase-js auth
# storage key: sb-stub-auth-token — the suite seeds a session under that key.
VITE_SUPABASE_PROJECT_ID="stub"
VITE_SUPABASE_URL="https://stub.supabase.co"
VITE_SUPABASE_PUBLISHABLE_KEY="stub-anon-key-not-a-secret"
